<TITLE> Vegetables trader mugged, killed in Tejgaon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 3 (bdnews24.com)--A vegetables trader was killed and younger brother critically wounded when a mugger stabbed them at Bijoy Sarani in Dhaka's Tejgaon in the early hours of Thursday. The trader has been named Monir Hossain, 22, who lived in Mirpur, and his brother Alauddin Hossain, 17. The victim's uncle Toriqul Islam said Monir and Alauddin were attacked by the muggers on their way to Kawran Bazar to receive vegetables around 1:30am. The mugger stabbed them and snatched Tk 7,000 and mobile phones from them, he said. Passersby took the brothers to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where the doctors declared Monir dead. Alauddin's condition was critical. Sub-inspector Mohammed Sadequl of Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Police Station said a case had been, but no one had been arrested yet
